Aizen2468 I have to say that this is one of the best adaptations of a book I have ever seen. It's very well done, and I congratulate all involved in bringing one of my favourite stories to the screen so expertly.  The main problem I see, which is the cause of other problems, is that they simply cannot include as much detail in the TV series as there is in the books. The Song of Ice and Fire is and immensely complicated series, with incredibly diverse interweaving plot lines. It is impossible for them to include this much in a series of standard format.   This creates issues when it comes to following the story, as some details are missed which are relevant later. They may not be vital for the story, but make it easier to understand. I can't think of any off the top of my head, but I have noticed several throughout. Having read the books, I have been able to explain why characters are acting a particular way when asked by friends who have only watched the series.   Part of me can't figure out how anyone could follow the story at all by just watching the series. When reading the books, I quickly realised I needed to keep flipping back to remind myself of details in order to follow parts of the story. It is one of my favourite epics of all time, but it is definitely not an easy read.
